parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent ABS and Brake Light Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the ABS and brake lights can cause the driver to lose confidence in the vehicle's braking system, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The ABS and brake lights on the dashboard come on and go off randomly
sometimes staying on for days at a time
and then going off for a day or two. The brakes may feel spongy or soft
and the stopping distance may increase.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A brake fluid reservoir leak can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake fluid reservoir leaks brake fluid
causing the brake and ABS lights to come on. The stopping distance may increase
and the brakes may feel spongy or soft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
and the brakes may feel spongy or soft. The stopping distance may increase
and the vehicle may jerk or vibrate when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear axle cracks or breaks
causing the vehicle to vibrate
make loud noises
and potentially lose control. The tires may also wear unevenly or become misaligned.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Rear Axle Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair of the rear axle recall can lead to continued safety risks, including loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear axle repair was not performed correctly
or the repair did not fully address the safety issue
leading to continued problems with the rear axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience erratic behavior, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gauges are acting erratically
the engine jerks or stalls
the interior lights flicker
the battery drains
and the ABS and brake lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS and brake lights illuminate
the brakes fail to respond
and the braking distance is reduced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel can cause the driver to lose critical information about the vehicle's operation, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gauges are acting erratically
the speedometer needle sticks or pegs
and the instrument panel lights are malfunctioning.
